# Role: content-publishing-engineer

> **Owns:** Tech Talk Management — Admin create, publish, edit (→ resets to Draft), republish, delete; plus the public Tech Talk listing/detail pages and admin form.
> Do not create or modify files outside the Owned Paths below without a PR reviewed by someone currently holding this role.

## Role Charter
Tech Talks are admin-authored content with their own, simpler publish cycle (Draft ⇄ Published), distinct from the author/reviewer article workflow. You own this pipeline end to end, backend and frontend both.

## Owned Paths
```
src/controllers/techTalkController.ts
src/services/techTalkService.ts
src/repositories/techTalkRepository.ts
src/routes/techTalksRoutes.ts
src/app/(dashboard)/techTalks/page.tsx
src/app/(dashboard)/techTalks/[id]/page.tsx
src/app/(dashboard)/admin/techTalks/page.tsx
src/components/techTalks/
```

## Project Context
- Stack: Next.js + TypeScript (FE), Express + TypeScript (BE), Neon PostgreSQL
- Auth: import `authenticate` and `requireRole` from `authentication-engineer` / `authorization-engineer` — never rewrite them
- API prefix: `/api/v1/`

## Status Machine
```
[Draft] ──publish──→ [Published]
   ↑
   └─── (Admin edits) ──→ [Draft]  (editing resets to Draft automatically)
```

## Strict Rules
1. Only **Admin** can create, edit, publish, republish, or delete Tech Talks.
2. Editing a Published Tech Talk automatically resets status to `Draft`.
3. Republish = explicit action to re-publish after editing (`POST /republish`).
4. Delete requires a `<ConfirmationModal>` (shared component).
5. Soft delete: set `deleted_at`, never hard delete.
6. Published Tech Talks sorted by `event_date DESC` by default; support title search, date sort, title sort.
7. `analytics-dashboard-engineer`'s homepage feed calls your repository for published tech talks — don't let them re-implement that query; keep the interface stable.

```typescript
// src/services/techTalkService.ts
async update(id: string, updates: TechTalkUpdateInput, adminId: string): Promise<TechTalk> {
  const existing = await techTalkRepository.findById(id);
  if (!existing) throw new AppError('Tech Talk not found', 404);
  return techTalkRepository.update(id, {
    ...updates,
    status: 'Draft',
    updatedAt: new Date(),
  });
}

async publish(id: string): Promise<TechTalk> {
  const talk = await techTalkRepository.findById(id);
  if (!talk) throw new AppError('Tech Talk not found', 404);
  if (talk.status === 'Published') throw new AppError('Already published', 400);
  return techTalkRepository.updateStatus(id, 'Published');
}
```

```typescript
interface TechTalk {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  description: string;
  presenters: string[];
  tags: string[];
  eventDate: Date;
  slidesUrl: string | null;
  youtubeUrl: string | null;
  status: 'Draft' | 'Published';
  createdBy: string;
  deletedAt: Date | null;
  createdAt: Date;
  updatedAt: Date;
}
```

